{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/2021/01/camunda-cockpit-history-plugin/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Asko Soukka","author":"Asko Soukka"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"29bd8a47-f8d5-5df5-a609-645545d27a5a","excerpt":"Year 2020 was a good year to learn business process automation possibilities with BPMN and Camunda – an open-source workflow and decision automation platform…","html":"<p>Year 2020 was a good year to learn business process automation possibilities with BPMN and <a href=\"https://camunda.com/\">Camunda</a> – an open-source workflow and decision automation platform. Not only were the related conferences online and free to attend, but good feature releases made the Camunda platform easier to adopt and extend.</p>\n<p>A possible challenge in starting business process automation with Camunda BPM is, that its free and open source user interfaces are limited to show only running/uncompleted process instances. Once process instance has been completed, or it has been canceled, it disappears from Camunda user interfaces (unless you have subscribed to their commercial enterprise version).</p>\n<p>Lucky us, thanks to the <a href=\"https://camunda.com/blog/2020/08/all-new-frontend-plugin-system-for-cockpit-starting-with-camunda-bpm-7-14/\">new plugin plugin system introduced in Camunda BPM 7.14.0</a>, it is now easier than ever to <a href=\"https://github.com/datakurre/camunda-cockpit-plugins/\">make at least some process history visible</a> also in the open source version:</p>\n<p><img src=\"/af4f4dbd52059a65be52ac4b1e5d56a8/camunda-cockpit-history-plugin.gif\" alt=\"Minimal Camunda Cockpit History Plugin\"></p>\n<p>I am sure that <a href=\"https://github.com/datakurre/camunda-cockpit-plugins/\">my plugins</a> are far cry from the official commercial offerings (which I have never seen or used myself). Yet, I believe that, even in their initial state, they should smooth the experience of getting started with BPMN based <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Robotic_process_automation#Hyperautomation\">“hyperautomation”</a> and Camunda BPM.</p>\n<h2>Try out the plugins</h2>\n<p>The easiest way to try my plugins yourself, is probably the new <a href=\"https://docs.camunda.org/manual/latest/user-guide/camunda-bpm-run/\">Camunda BPM Run</a> -distribution.</p>\n<p>At first, download and unpack the distribution:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\">\n      <pre class=\" cm-s-solarized\"><code><span>$ curl -LO https://downloads.camunda.cloud/release/camunda-bpm/run/7.14/camunda-bpm-run-7.14.0.tar.gz\n$ tar xzvf camunda-bpm-run-7.14.0.tar.gz</span></code></pre>\n    </div>\n<p>Next, download a simple example process model:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\">\n      <pre class=\" cm-s-solarized\"><code><span>$ curl -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/camunda/camunda-bpm-examples/master/usertask/task-form-generated/src/main/resources/loanApproval.bpmn -o configuration/resources/loanApproval.bpmn</span></code></pre>\n    </div>\n<p>Now, prepare a temporary directory structure for the plugin:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\">\n      <pre class=\" cm-s-solarized\"><code><span>$ mkdir -p META-INF/resources/webjars/camunda/app/cockpit/scripts/</span></code></pre>\n    </div>\n<p>Then, download the built versions of my plugins (at the time of this writing):</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\">\n      <pre class=\" cm-s-solarized\"><code><span>$ curl -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datakurre/camunda-cockpit-plugins/825566a3544f637225140bff14aa23ca84843194/definition-historic-activities.js -o META-INF/resources/webjars/camunda/app/cockpit/scripts/definition-historic-activities.js\n$ curl -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datakurre/camunda-cockpit-plugins/825566a3544f637225140bff14aa23ca84843194/instance-historic-activities.js -o META-INF/resources/webjars/camunda/app/cockpit/scripts/instance-historic-activities.js\n$ curl -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datakurre/camunda-cockpit-plugins/825566a3544f637225140bff14aa23ca84843194/instance-route-history.js -o META-INF/resources/webjars/camunda/app/cockpit/scripts/instance-route-history.js\n$ curl -L https://raw.githubusercontent.com/datakurre/camunda-cockpit-plugins/825566a3544f637225140bff14aa23ca84843194/config.js -o META-INF/resources/webjars/camunda/app/cockpit/scripts/config.js</span></code></pre>\n    </div>\n<p>Finally, update the webapps with these plugins:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"bash\">\n      <pre class=\" cm-s-solarized\"><code><span>$ jar uf internal/webapps/camunda-webapp-webjar-7.14.0.jar META-INF</span></code></pre>\n    </div>\n<p>and start Camunda:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"null\">\n      <pre class=\" cm-s-solarized\"><code><span>$ bash start.sh</span></code></pre>\n    </div>\n<p>That’s it.</p>\n<p>Since these are completely front-end plugins running on the browser, they should not have any side-effects for the process engine itself. Also, <a href=\"https://github.com/datakurre/camunda-cockpit-plugins/\">the repository itself</a>, could work as an example for developing plugins with ReactJS in TypeScript (filenames are subject to change):</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><code>definition-historic-activities.js</code> plugin bundle adds diagram badges for the 100 latest activities from Camunda process history on the currently viewed process definition, and a new Statistics tab to show some statistics from those activities. The limit of 100 latest activities is just a safe guess, usually enough for learning purposes (and subject to be increased and removed once the plugin evolves)\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/b53e422c4014903335069d3bde66ac87/4352a/camunda-cockpit-definition-statistics.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.67567567567568%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Historic activities badges and definition statistics tab\"\n        title=\"Historic activities badges and definition statistics tab\"\n        src=\"/static/b53e422c4014903335069d3bde66ac87/fcda8/camunda-cockpit-definition-statistics.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/b53e422c4014903335069d3bde66ac87/12f09/camunda-cockpit-definition-statistics.png 148w,\n/static/b53e422c4014903335069d3bde66ac87/e4a3f/camunda-cockpit-definition-statistics.png 295w,\n/static/b53e422c4014903335069d3bde66ac87/fcda8/camunda-cockpit-definition-statistics.png 590w,\n/static/b53e422c4014903335069d3bde66ac87/efc66/camunda-cockpit-definition-statistics.png 885w,\n/static/b53e422c4014903335069d3bde66ac87/c83ae/camunda-cockpit-definition-statistics.png 1180w,\n/static/b53e422c4014903335069d3bde66ac87/4352a/camunda-cockpit-definition-statistics.png 1364w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><code>instance-historic-activities.js</code> plugin bundle adds diagram badges for all historic activities on the currentlty viewed process instance, and a new Audit Log tab to show same data from the completed activitites</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4b3a40ac9d03758caecf8edf31a97592/4352a/camunda-cockpit-process-log.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.67567567567568%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Historic activities badges and process log tab\"\n        title=\"Historic activities badges and process log tab\"\n        src=\"/static/4b3a40ac9d03758caecf8edf31a97592/fcda8/camunda-cockpit-process-log.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4b3a40ac9d03758caecf8edf31a97592/12f09/camunda-cockpit-process-log.png 148w,\n/static/4b3a40ac9d03758caecf8edf31a97592/e4a3f/camunda-cockpit-process-log.png 295w,\n/static/4b3a40ac9d03758caecf8edf31a97592/fcda8/camunda-cockpit-process-log.png 590w,\n/static/4b3a40ac9d03758caecf8edf31a97592/efc66/camunda-cockpit-process-log.png 885w,\n/static/4b3a40ac9d03758caecf8edf31a97592/c83ae/camunda-cockpit-process-log.png 1180w,\n/static/4b3a40ac9d03758caecf8edf31a97592/4352a/camunda-cockpit-process-log.png 1364w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><code>instance-route-history.js</code> plugin bundle adds a new History tab on process definition view to list the 100 latest historic process instances for the currently viewed process definition and a link to open those instances (even the completed ones) for a limited process instance view (with the diagram and some information tabs)</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d8e9d617f8cef313ee591a1257058b8a/4352a/camunda-cockpit-definition-history.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.67567567567568%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Historic process instances tab\"\n        title=\"Historic process instances tab\"\n        src=\"/static/d8e9d617f8cef313ee591a1257058b8a/fcda8/camunda-cockpit-definition-history.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d8e9d617f8cef313ee591a1257058b8a/12f09/camunda-cockpit-definition-history.png 148w,\n/static/d8e9d617f8cef313ee591a1257058b8a/e4a3f/camunda-cockpit-definition-history.png 295w,\n/static/d8e9d617f8cef313ee591a1257058b8a/fcda8/camunda-cockpit-definition-history.png 590w,\n/static/d8e9d617f8cef313ee591a1257058b8a/efc66/camunda-cockpit-definition-history.png 885w,\n/static/d8e9d617f8cef313ee591a1257058b8a/c83ae/camunda-cockpit-definition-history.png 1180w,\n/static/d8e9d617f8cef313ee591a1257058b8a/4352a/camunda-cockpit-definition-history.png 1364w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/45dd4ef9dd1e5b5af7327a90b64c10a4/4352a/camunda-cockpit-historic-process.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 50.67567567567568%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"Historic process instance view\"\n        title=\"Historic process instance view\"\n        src=\"/static/45dd4ef9dd1e5b5af7327a90b64c10a4/fcda8/camunda-cockpit-historic-process.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/45dd4ef9dd1e5b5af7327a90b64c10a4/12f09/camunda-cockpit-historic-process.png 148w,\n/static/45dd4ef9dd1e5b5af7327a90b64c10a4/e4a3f/camunda-cockpit-historic-process.png 295w,\n/static/45dd4ef9dd1e5b5af7327a90b64c10a4/fcda8/camunda-cockpit-historic-process.png 590w,\n/static/45dd4ef9dd1e5b5af7327a90b64c10a4/efc66/camunda-cockpit-historic-process.png 885w,\n/static/45dd4ef9dd1e5b5af7327a90b64c10a4/c83ae/camunda-cockpit-historic-process.png 1180w,\n/static/45dd4ef9dd1e5b5af7327a90b64c10a4/4352a/camunda-cockpit-historic-process.png 1364w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>finally <code>config.js</code> is an example Camunda Cockpit plugin configuration with configuration to enable the above plugin bundles.</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>For questions, please, just open <a href=\"https://github.com/datakurre/camunda-cockpit-plugins/issues\">a new issue</a> or <a href=\"https://forum.camunda.org/\">a new dicussion thread</a>.</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Open source “history plugin” for Camunda Cockpit","date":"January 03, 2021"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/2021/01/camunda-cockpit-history-plugin/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/2020/07/camunda-run-robocloud-setup/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Setting up Camunda Run and connecting with Robocloud"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/2021/03/implementing-user-epics-bpmn-plone-volto/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Implementing user epics with BPMN"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454"]}